
@startuml

' Entities
class School {
    +String name
}

class Teacher {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
    +String email
}

class Student {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
}

class Person {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
}

abstract class Room {
    +String name
}

class Classroom extends Room {
    +int capacity
}

class OtherRoom extends Room {
    +double sizeInSquareMeters
}

class ClassGroup {
    +String name
}

' Associations and relationships

' Inheritance
Person <|-- Teacher
Person <|-- Student

' Composition/Aggregation
School "1" *- "many" Room : has
School "1" *- "many" Teacher : employs
School "1" *- "many" Student : enrolls
School "1" o-- "1" Teacher : principal
Teacher "0..3" --> "1" School : teaches at
Teacher "0..1" o-- "1" School : is principal of

Student "1" --> "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
ClassGroup "1" --> "1" Classroom : uses
ClassGroup "1" *- "10..31" Student : contains

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **`Person`** is an abstract class that both `Teacher` and `Student` inherit from.
- **`School`** has attributes and relations to `Teacher`, `Student`, `Room`, and one `Teacher` as its principal.
- A **`Teacher`** can be in up to 3 schools and only 1 principal role.
- A **`Student`** is enrolled in exactly one school and one class group.
- A **`ClassGroup`** contains between 10–31 students, has a name (e.g., 5a), and is assigned to one classroom.
- **`Room`** is an abstract base for `Classroom` and `OtherRoom`.
- Multiplicities are used where constraints exist (e.g., `10..31`, `0..1`, `1..*`, etc.).

